WearEver-ProctorSilex Inc saidit will relocate is corporate headquarters from Chillicothe toRichmond, Va., beginning this fall and ending by early 1988.    The company said Richmond was chosen because it iscentrally located to its main operating facilities, which willreduce travel and other costs.    About 150 headquarters employees will be offered the chanceto relocate, the company said. WearEver's cookware plant inChillicothe will not be moved, and its sales and marketingoffices will remain in Englewood, N.J. Reuter&#3;